Health minister Zweli Mkhize is in the Free State. The province has reported its first coronavirus case. The minister is checking on screening processes. He's briefing the media on that as well as giving an update on national COVID-19 numbers. • Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. Watch the recording above. BLOEMFONTEIN - The number of people infected by the coronavirus in South Africa has soared to 202. There are 52 new infections with Gauteng still being the epicenter of the virus. Over 60-percent of South Africans will feel the direct impact of COVID-19, even if they don't contract the virus. READ: No COVID-19 vaccine yet: Health minister More local transmissions are being recorded. The Free State and Limpopo have confirmed their first cases. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.